{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:psalms.7",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 7 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:1",
      "text": "A Psalm of David, which he sang to the Lord because of the words of Chusi the",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:2",
      "text": "O Lord my God, in thee have I trusted: save me from all them that persecute me, and deliver me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:3",
      "text": "Lest at any time the enemy seize my soul as a lion, while there is none to ransom, nor to save.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:4",
      "text": "O Lord my God, if I have done this; (if there is unrighteousness in my hands;)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:5",
      "text": "if I have requited with evil those who requited me with good; may I then perish empty by means of my enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:6",
      "text": "Let the enemy persecute my soul, and take it; and let him trample my life on the ground, and lay my glory in the dust. Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:7",
      "text": "Arise, O Lord, in thy wrath; be exalted in the utmost boundaries of mine enemies: awake, O Lord my God, according to the decree which thou didst command.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:8",
      "text": "And the congregation of the nations shall compass thee: and for this cause do thou return on high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:9",
      "text": "The Lord shall judge the nations: judge me, O Lord, according to my righteousness, and according to my innocence that is in me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:10",
      "text": "Oh let the wickedness of sinners come to an end; and then thou shalt direct the righteous, O God that searchest the hearts and reins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:11",
      "text": "My help is righteous, coming from God who saves the upright in heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:12",
      "text": "God is a righteous judge, and strong, and patient, not inflicting vengeance every day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:13",
      "text": "If ye will not repent, he will furbish his sword; he has bent his bow, and made it ready.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:14",
      "text": "And on it he has fitted the instruments of death; he has completed his arrows for the raging ones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:15",
      "text": "Behold, he has travailed with unrighteousness, he has conceived trouble, and brought forth iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:16",
      "text": "He has opened a pit, and dug it up, and he shall fall into the ditch which he has made. perhaps 'persecuting ones.'",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:17",
      "text": "His trouble shall return on his own head, and his unrighteousness shall come down on his own crown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:psalms.7.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 7:18",
      "text": "I will give thanks to the Lord according to his righteousness; I will sing to the name of the Lord most high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
